1
00:00:04,157 --> 00:00:06,665
How can we deny individuality?

2
00:00:06,665 --> 00:00:09,053
Look at all the individuals 
in this room.

3
00:00:09,299 --> 00:00:12,420
[The Body | Karmic Dress]

4
00:00:12,835 --> 00:00:14,216
But then,
it’s to understand:

5
00:00:14,216 --> 00:00:16,540
are we the clothes 
that we wear?

6
00:00:16,540 --> 00:00:19,849
Is that what defines us, 
our dress?

7
00:00:21,188 --> 00:00:24,622
Well, I mean it does
to a certain degree.

8
00:00:24,622 --> 00:00:26,804
What you wear defines you.

9
00:00:26,804 --> 00:00:29,274
So you can say,
yes, dress defines,

10
00:00:29,274 --> 00:00:33,700
but shall that be 
the exclusive marker

11
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:36,682
for defining an individual,

12
00:00:36,682 --> 00:00:39,044
is how they dress?

13
00:00:39,044 --> 00:00:42,747
No. That would be absurd
to suggest that.

14
00:00:42,747 --> 00:00:46,077
So, if we look,
that’s literally clothes.

15
00:00:46,077 --> 00:00:46,920
Then we’re told,

16
00:00:46,920 --> 00:00:50,332
tamasā bahurūpeṇa veṣṭitāḥ karmahetunā—
[Ms: 1.49a]

17
00:00:50,338 --> 00:00:53,220
the body is karmic dress.

18
00:00:53,232 --> 00:00:57,056
Shall that be the means
to define an individual?

19
00:00:57,056 --> 00:01:00,780
Well, no. It should be,
we can’t deny—

20
00:01:00,780 --> 00:01:03,081
someone’s a human being, 
someone’s a dog,

21
00:01:03,081 --> 00:01:05,822
someone is a tree.

22
00:01:06,942 --> 00:01:10,164
And we’re responsible
for the karmic dress

23
00:01:10,164 --> 00:01:12,581
we’re situated in at present.

24
00:01:12,581 --> 00:01:16,620
But if we limit 
defining ourselves to that,

25
00:01:16,620 --> 00:01:19,859
that would be as if to limit 
defining ourselves

26
00:01:19,859 --> 00:01:21,997
to the clothes
that we’re wearing.

27
00:01:22,020 --> 00:01:23,976
Why should we do that?

28
00:01:24,269 --> 00:01:26,703
So this simple type of analysis,

29
00:01:26,703 --> 00:01:29,940
you don’t have to be a genius
to follow this.

30
00:01:29,940 --> 00:01:34,896
So, if it’s then not the body 
that defines the self, ātma,

31
00:01:34,896 --> 00:01:39,773
it’s not the mind that defines the self,
or the intellect,

32
00:01:39,773 --> 00:01:44,263
then we start approaching
where the soul is located.

33
00:01:44,275 --> 00:01:47,940
So, how that soul 
should proceed

34
00:01:47,940 --> 00:01:51,020
on the basis
of their individual position?

35
00:01:51,020 --> 00:01:54,143
How should they make progress
and move forward?

36
00:01:54,143 --> 00:01:57,820
Where will they get that 
direction from?

37
00:01:57,820 --> 00:02:03,016
From the acquired tendency 
they have?

38
00:02:03,016 --> 00:02:04,502
The way
they’ve been calibrated

39
00:02:04,502 --> 00:02:07,813
by their false ego and 
acquired prejudice and tendency

40
00:02:07,813 --> 00:02:10,743
to read 
environmental circumstances—

41
00:02:10,743 --> 00:02:13,862
will that be the best way
for them to proceed?

42
00:02:13,862 --> 00:02:15,569
I don’t think so.

43
00:02:16,139 --> 00:02:18,081
They’re getting false readings.

44
00:02:18,081 --> 00:02:22,863
False ego means the false read
of the environment,

45
00:02:23,047 --> 00:02:27,742
who you are, 
and what your relationship is.

46
00:02:28,546 --> 00:02:35,022
And, for lack of a better word, 
it’s unscientific.

47
00:02:35,022 --> 00:02:38,382
It wouldn’t be acceptable
in science,

48
00:02:38,382 --> 00:02:40,302
you’d have to recalibrate.

49
00:02:40,302 --> 00:02:44,691
So spiritual culture is about
recalibrating your position

50
00:02:44,691 --> 00:02:48,382
on the basis 
of your reality potential

51
00:02:48,382 --> 00:02:51,376
as a soul 
in self-expression;

52
00:02:51,376 --> 00:02:55,577
a dedicating unit,
a unit that’s capable of dedicating

53
00:02:55,577 --> 00:03:00,500
every atom of its existence
to something higher.

54
00:03:00,500 --> 00:03:06,822
Not trying to devour, to acquire, 
control and consume

55
00:03:06,822 --> 00:03:12,683
things which are lower,
to produce satisfaction,

56
00:03:12,687 --> 00:03:17,020
but to dedicate oneself 
to something higher

57
00:03:17,020 --> 00:03:19,914
as a means of achieving 
self-fulfillment,

58
00:03:19,914 --> 00:03:22,704
self-realisation, self-satisfaction.

